New York Times bestselling author Sarah MacLean returns with the next Hell’s Belles novel about a chaotic bluestocking and the buttoned-up detective enlisted to keep her out of trouble (spoiler: She is the trouble). 
With her headful of wild curls and wilder ideas and an unabashed love of experiments and explosives, society has labeled Lady Imogen Loveless peculiar…and doesn’t know she’s one of the Hell’s Belles—a group of vigilantes operating outside the notice of most of London.

Thomas Peck is not most of London. The brilliant detective fought his way off the streets and into a promising career through sheer force of will and a keen ability to see things others miss, like the fact that Imogen isn’t peculiar…she’s pandemonium. If you ask him, she requires a keeper. When her powerful family discovers her late-night activities, they couldn’t agree more…and they know just the man for the task.

Thomas wants nothing to do with guarding Imogen. He is a grown man with a proper job and no time for the lady’s incendiary chaos, no matter how lushly it is packaged. But some assignments are too explosive to pass up, and the gruff detective is soon caught up in Imogen’s world, full of her bold smiles and burning secrets…and a fiery passion that threatens to consume them both.

What’s happening in Florida’s schools and libraries is just the tip of the iceberg — there is a massive, draconian movement across the United States to ban books — and particularly those by and about LGBTQIA+ and BIPOC people. 

What’s more, challenges are likely underreported, because librarians who are resisting them are facing unprecedented workplace retribution and in some cases physical danger.

In 2022, book bans in United States schools and libraries were at their highest since the American Library Association’s Office of Intellectual Freedom started collecting data. Bans are happening around the country, in every state. 

But we can help. 

Scroll for information, resources and organizations that are supporting teachers, students and families on the front line of this fight. Follow and subscribe to these organizations and their newsletters. Get informed about what’s happening in your own town and remember…you don’t have to be a parent or a teacher to go to school board meetings and stand with the kids and teachers who are speaking out. 

This is the first of two posts — there were more organizations than Instagram would let me post in one patch! 

Feel free to share widely.
❤️❤️

It’s hard to find the words to explain how gutted I am to hear that Julie Garwood passed away last week. 

When I say I wouldn’t be here without her, I mean that — her characters, her worlds and her books have inspired me as a reader, a writer and a person, reminding me that there is humor and light and hope and love in the world, and that happily ever after is a worthy, wonderful goal. All that, and she definitely hardwired “Mine” into my psyche with The Bride.

I was lucky enough to meet her once and to tell her this — she was immensely gracious and pretended not to notice that I cried the whole time we talked. 

My thoughts are with her family and friends, and with all the other readers who were changed because of her gorgeous stories. 

❤️

💘Two people who are absolutely gone for each other
🍿A group of friends who clock it from the start and get popcorn
👊Justifiable face punching
🦸‍♂️An exasperated bodyguard of a hero
💃A heroine who has no intention of being body guarded
🗣️Banter--my god, these two and their BANTER just get a room already! (spoiler: they get a room)
🛌Only one bed in a London snowstorm 
💪Me and you against the patriarchy
💥💥💥💥

I hope you’ll love this one as much as I do. I am so so thrilled to share it with you, because I miss these two a whole lot, and I can’t wait for y’all to meet them.

If your book has literally gone “boom!,” I’d like to make it right! Please send an email to avonromance@harpercollins.com with a photo of your damaged book, your name and mailing address. Thank you so so much for your patience, and I hope you are enjoying the read, and really getting the full Imogen chaos experience!  Now you know how hard it is to be Tommy!

START YOUR ROMANCE NOVEL TODAY
October 29, 2023, 1PM EST

Join New York Times and USA Today bestselling romance novelist Sarah MacLean for this two-hour live, online course covering everything you’ll need to start your romance novel today. The class will survey the entrypoints to great romance storytelling, the development of memorable characters, undeniable chemistry and strong conflict, and tips and tricks to avoid pitfalls and keep the pages turning and the words flowing as you draft.

This course runs October 29, just in time for #NaNoWriMo, and is perfect for a range of beginners—from those who are already drafting to those who have a seed of an idea to those who simply think they’d like to try writing a romance. It includes an opportunity to ask Sarah your own questions about writing and one-month access to a video recording of the session.
Read about this perfect match now, wherever you get your books! sarahmaclean.net/knockout

My brother would’ve turned 53 today, and I would’ve sent him a dozen silly birthday texts, and called and sung him happy birthday very loudly and off key, and told him V’s plan to take him to see The Marvels on Friday, which had been in the works for a year.

Tell people you love them. Do it so much it’s kind of weird. You won’t regret it.

❤️

Artists need to create on the same scale as society has the capacity to destroy. 

Spotted in Brooklyn

I’m not quite sure how this happened, as I’m pretty sure my own 10th birthday—complete with mixtapes and a bubblegum pink boom box— was just a heartbeat ago.

Love you, bug. You’re my favorite thing. ❤️

BIG NEWS!

 If you’ve been waiting to start a MacLean series, or you haven’t been sure if historical is for you, you can get The Bareknuckle Bastards free with your monthly Kindle Unlimited subscription for a very limited time! 

Now’s your chance to read my lady lockpick and hardened criminal (Wicked & the Wallflower), to find out exactly who ties whom to a mast 🔥🔥🔥 (Brazen & the Beast), and to watch a villain crawl over broken glass for the woman he loves (Daring & the Duke).

Many believe that this is the best series to enter the MacLeaniverse, so put it on your 2024 TBR — I hope this reading resolution will be easy to keep!
